<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><template xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="openEHR/v1/Template" xmlns:uuid="java:java.util.UUID"><id>5da1c989-2d0a-48b4-99ee-fe1e16912604</id><name>Diagnostic Imaging - Magnetic Resonance - MR Intra-Surgery with and without Enhancement Order</name><description><lifecycle_state>Initial</lifecycle_state><details><purpose>For ordering a(n) MR Intra-Surgery with and without Enhancement</purpose><use/><misuse/></details><other_details><item><key>MetaDataSet:Sample Set </key><value>Template metadata sample set </value></item><item><key>Acknowledgements</key><value/></item><item><key>Business Process Level</key><value/></item><item><key>Care setting</key><value/></item><item><key>Client group</key><value/></item><item><key>Clinical Record Element</key><value/></item><item><key>Copyright</key><value/></item><item><key>Issues</key><value/></item><item><key>Owner</key><value/></item><item><key>Sign off</key><value/></item><item><key>Speciality</key><value/></item><item><key>User roles</key><value/></item></other_details></description><annotations path="[openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1]"><items><item><key>Imaging.Body Part</key><value>%=HD</value></item><item><key>Imaging.Laterality</key><value>No</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Patient Requirements</key><value>Laboratory: Creatinine LEVEL and eGFR required within three months of exam. Required for patients with known or suspected renal impairment/failure.;Nutrition: Operating room/surgery provides instructions on fasting guidelines.;IV requirements: Venous access required, infusion pump disconnected. Contact OR department for further instructions.;Medications: Patient cooperative/able to hold still with appropriate pain management and oral sedation as required. Discontinue medications running through pumps prior to MRI procedure. If pumps are unable to be discontinued, please contact the MRI department for further instructions. Continue oral medications as ordered.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Communication</key><value>MRI Patient History, Screening Form and signed consent form (if required) to be completed by patient, family member or designate and sent to the MRI department prior to patient arrival. If the patient is unable to complete screening form and/or give consent independently, ensure that a legal procedure consent form is provided and contact MRI department for further instructions. Patient in hospital attire with no metal pins, buttons or fasteners. The patient must remove all metal items before coming to the MRI department. This includes pins, hairpieces, jewellery, makeup, prostheses, wallets or phones. The patient may keep their glasses, false teeth, and hearing aids but these will be removed prior to the MRI exam.  Complete patient chart, including current medication record, must accompany patient to the MRI department. If required for interpretation/translation, patient safety, or comfort, family members accompanying patients will be required to complete the MRI screening form in the MRI OR department.  Nursing accompaniment if required. Pediatric: Parent/legal guardian should accompany the patient.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Resources </key><value>http://insite.albertahealthservices.ca/assets/policy/clp-di-prov-dimr3-0-gad-admin-renal-impair.pdf</value></item></items></annotations><definition xsi:type="INSTRUCTION" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1" concept_name="Service request" max="1" name="MR Intra-Surgery with and without Enhancement"/><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">B48161A11EF4549FFAE82EE73B385AF5</digest></integrity_checks><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.service_request_information.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">230A8D964017E1FD7AC82EBDEE0202A6</digest></integrity_checks></template>